    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering an exceptional 2002 BMW M3 (E46), a benchmark of atmospheric engineering. This example features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, boasting individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. The dual-VANOS system has been professionally serviced, and the subframe has received comprehensive reinforcement to ensure structural rigidity under high-torque conditions. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a mechanical limited-slip differential. The exterior retains its factory depth with zero imperfections, while the interior features Nappa leather with pristine bolsters and fully operational switchgear. Mechanically flawless, this M3 demonstrates linear power delivery and precise turn-in, representing a collector-grade specimen for those who prioritize mechanical provenance.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Garage kept. Full service records. No accidents. Clean title. Inspections welcome.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "This vehicle is an absolute masterpiece of automotive preservation, presenting in a state that can only be described as showroom-fresh. Every inch of the exterior paint retains its original deep luster, free from even the slightest swirl marks or stone chips, thanks to a lifetime of climate-controlled garage storage and a professional ceramic coating. The interior is equally pristine; the premium leather upholstery remains supple and matte, devoid of the typical wear or creasing found in used vehicles, and the cabin still carries that distinct new-car aroma. Mechanically, the car is beyond reproach. It has been maintained with an open-checkbook policy, with every service milestone documented and performed by master technicians. From the crisp engagement of the switchgear to the silent, powerful delivery of the engine, this car drives exactly as it did the day it was delivered. This is a rare opportunity to own a collector-grade example that includes all original keys, manuals, and a bespoke car cover.",
      "price": 48500.0,
