    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This E46 M3 represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated Bavarian engineering. Under the hood, the S54B32 straight-six remains in pristine mechanical health, delivering linear power through its six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. The ZF 6-speed manual transmission provides tactile, short-throw shifts, paired with a factory limited-slip differential for optimal torque distribution. This example features a reinforced rear subframe and a refreshed suspension geometry utilizing Bilstein dampers to maintain factory-plus kinematics. With zero oxidation on the undercarriage and a factory-spec finish, this chassis remains structurally flawless, offering the telepathic steering response and high-revving engagement that defines the M-division's golden era.",
